<h1>Winter runs.</h1>  
<p>Because of the severe frosts I was forced not to run for the whole week (if, of course, donâ€™t consider as running  the movements on the streets in such weather). And now the frosts are over and I finally went for a run. After any run, you feel all you muscles separately and at the same time you feel your entire body as one whole. But after the winter run, you additionally experience the pleasantness after you've breathed a lot of frosty air and the euphoria from what you have achieved. And these are insanely cool feelings!</p>